  "beneficiary": "Building Worker, Construction Worker",
  "details": "The scheme 'Medical Assistance/Wage Compensation during Illness' is implemented by the Haryana Building and Other Construction Workers Welfare Board (HBOCWWB). Under this scheme, wage compensation/financial assistance is provided to registered construction workers as per the prevailing minimum wages in the state in case of an accident or illness. This assistance applies if the registered worker is admitted to a government or government-approved private hospital for treatment for a period ranging from 4 to 30 days.",
